WEBVTT

00:01.418 --> 00:02.753
<i>Previously on "The Watchful Eye"...</i>

00:02.753 --> 00:04.171
People have felt a malevolent
presence in the basement

00:04.171 --> 00:05.923
from Alistair Greybourne himself.

00:05.923 --> 00:07.716
Jocelyn tells Alistair
that she suspects

00:07.716 --> 00:09.635
that Winthrop
stole her treasure.

00:09.635 --> 00:11.470
- Jocelyn.
- Who's Jocelyn?

00:11.470 --> 00:12.888
She's the nanny that jumped
out of the window

00:12.888 --> 00:14.264
in the attic and died.

00:14.264 --> 00:15.933
I was talking to her
like I'm talking to you,

00:15.933 --> 00:18.143
except she's dead.

00:18.143 --> 00:19.645
But I never surfed
Tamarama Beach.

00:19.645 --> 00:21.063
What's Tamarama Beach?

00:21.063 --> 00:23.148
I grew up surfing there.

00:23.148 --> 00:25.025
Aah!

00:25.025 --> 00:26.526
I love you.

00:26.526 --> 00:28.195
We'll finish the job,
but you and me, we're done.

00:28.195 --> 00:31.031
Because of the Greybournes,
my dad took his own life.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.283
This place is starting
to push me over the edge.

00:33.283 --> 00:34.660
The Greybournes
and the Winthrops

00:34.660 --> 00:36.578
are all the same family.
Elena: Ruby Greybourne.

00:36.578 --> 00:41.542
♪

00:41.542 --> 00:42.960
Yeah, have a seat.

00:45.837 --> 00:48.090
Hey, how'd you find out
where I live?

00:48.090 --> 00:49.967
A friend at the City
Records Department.

00:49.967 --> 00:53.595
His boss uses "password"
for all of his passwords.

00:53.595 --> 00:55.097
It's not that hard
to find someone.

00:55.097 --> 00:56.598
Okay.

00:56.598 --> 00:58.100
You gonna tell me
why you came here?

00:58.100 --> 00:59.893
Why do you think I'm here,
Detective?

00:59.893 --> 01:01.353
Doorman fell
down the stairs?

01:01.353 --> 01:03.230
Maybe you saw something?
You want to make a statement?

01:03.230 --> 01:05.983
I didn't, and I don't.

01:05.983 --> 01:08.443
I know you and Elena
are a thing.

01:08.443 --> 01:09.945
I saw you together
at the bar.

01:09.945 --> 01:12.281
I mean, we used to be a thing,
but we're not anymore.

01:12.281 --> 01:13.991
Sorry to hear that.
Is she okay?

01:13.991 --> 01:15.033
I haven't talked to her
in a while.

01:15.033 --> 01:16.535
No, not really.

01:16.535 --> 01:18.870
She's getting mixed up
in some pretty scary stuff

01:18.870 --> 01:20.872
that I am now
mixed up into.

01:20.872 --> 01:22.583
Like what?

01:22.583 --> 01:24.668
She's at The Greybourne because
they messed with her family,

01:24.668 --> 01:28.046
and now her dad's dead and
she wants to get back at them.

01:28.046 --> 01:30.465
The Greybournes and Winthrops
are bad news.

01:30.465 --> 01:32.884
If she thinks she can take
a run at them, she's wrong.

01:32.884 --> 01:34.970
Can you talk to her?
Yeah.

01:34.970 --> 01:36.263
I mean--
She won't listen to me,

01:36.263 --> 01:39.433
and I just want her
to be okay.

01:39.433 --> 01:40.809
I mean, she doesn't really
listen to me either,

01:40.809 --> 01:42.894
but, yeah,
I can give it a try.

01:42.894 --> 01:44.730
Thanks.

01:44.730 --> 01:47.774
I'll see myself out.

01:47.774 --> 01:50.652
Hey, you're a good friend,
Ginny Welles.

01:50.652 --> 01:52.112
Yeah.

01:55.157 --> 01:57.367
[ Door opens ]

01:57.367 --> 01:58.577
[ Door closes ]

02:03.707 --> 02:05.959
Hey.
How was drop-off?

02:05.959 --> 02:07.544
All good.

02:07.544 --> 02:10.630
He's psyched about seeing
the flamingos and the elephants,

02:10.630 --> 02:11.965
and Flora's parents said
they won't give him

02:11.965 --> 02:13.508
too much cotton candy.

02:13.508 --> 02:16.511
Ah, we'll see.
Those two are pushovers.

02:16.511 --> 02:18.138
Ah, any plans
for your day off?

02:18.138 --> 02:21.433
Yeah,
just coffee and errands.

02:21.433 --> 02:24.227
Sounds fun.

02:24.227 --> 02:25.312
Yeah. Okay.

02:25.312 --> 02:27.064
Well, I'll see you.

02:28.815 --> 02:29.900
See ya.

02:38.492 --> 02:40.786
Hey.

02:40.786 --> 02:43.246
We got to talk.

02:43.246 --> 02:44.998
How did you hear
about it?

02:44.998 --> 02:46.249
The ruby specifically.

02:46.249 --> 02:48.043
How did you hear about it?

02:48.043 --> 02:49.628
I told you.
My grandmother.

02:49.628 --> 02:51.421
She said Alistair Greybourne
hid some secret treasure

02:51.421 --> 02:53.256
inside his building
before he died.

02:53.256 --> 02:56.218
A priceless ruby.

02:56.218 --> 02:58.553
Why? Did you--
you find the ruby?

03:00.472 --> 03:02.432
Not the one we wanted.

03:02.432 --> 03:05.060
What's this?

03:05.060 --> 03:06.269
Ruby Greybourne.

03:06.269 --> 03:10.190
Born August 21, 1945,
to parents

03:10.190 --> 03:13.110
Alistair Greybourne
and Jocelyn Morrow.

03:13.110 --> 03:14.528
What, Jocelyn the nanny?

03:14.528 --> 03:15.946
And her boss.

03:15.946 --> 03:17.072
I told you they were
having an affair.

03:17.072 --> 03:18.657
I guess
they had a kid, too.

03:18.657 --> 03:21.034
You're-- You're saying
that the ruby's a baby?

03:21.034 --> 03:22.202
Buried treasure.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.620
No, no, no, no, no.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.455
You just got to keep
looking for it.

03:25.455 --> 03:27.207
Scott, I tore
the place apart.

03:27.207 --> 03:28.250
Yeah, bullshit!

03:28.250 --> 03:29.709
Open your eyes!

03:29.709 --> 03:31.378
Jocelyn and Alistair
had a baby,

03:31.378 --> 03:32.838
and then
Jocelyn killed herself.

03:32.838 --> 03:34.047
And there isn't a ruby

03:34.047 --> 03:36.299
because there was never
a ruby to begin with!

03:36.299 --> 03:41.388
♪

03:46.935 --> 03:57.612
♪

03:57.612 --> 03:59.614
They cut us off
without a cent.

03:59.614 --> 04:01.158
My whole family, Elena.

04:05.162 --> 04:07.038
And then Allie was
gonna try to fix things.

04:07.038 --> 04:08.498
And then you.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.627
And our plan, th-that--
that was it.

04:12.627 --> 04:14.379
That was it.
There is no Plan "C."

04:14.379 --> 04:20.260
♪

04:20.260 --> 04:23.472
I wanted it so bad.

04:23.472 --> 04:26.600
To take something
from them...

04:26.600 --> 04:28.018
and just vanish.

04:32.272 --> 04:33.732
But I'm scared.

04:35.942 --> 04:37.611
If I get one more text

04:37.611 --> 04:41.448
threatening to hurt me
or Teo...

04:44.576 --> 04:46.328
I don't want
to do this anymore.

04:48.663 --> 04:50.373
I have to leave
The Greybourne.

04:53.126 --> 04:55.337
Yeah, well, your cover's
nearly blown anyhow, so...

04:57.589 --> 04:58.757
Your friend--
What's her name, Ginny--

04:58.757 --> 05:00.175
came by.

05:00.175 --> 05:01.760
What did you say?

05:01.760 --> 05:02.886
I didn't say anything,

05:02.886 --> 05:04.304
but you told her
a lot of shit, Elena.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.181
But for whatever reason,

05:06.181 --> 05:08.600
she really cares
about you, so...

05:08.600 --> 05:09.643
Good job.

05:09.643 --> 05:12.729
You really rooked her.

05:12.729 --> 05:16.066
Your mom would have
been proud.

05:16.066 --> 05:19.236
I have to wrap things up
with her.

05:19.236 --> 05:20.737
No.

05:20.737 --> 05:22.989
No, just pack up
and get out.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.659
I can't.
They'll come--

05:25.659 --> 05:27.577
They'll come looking
if I just disappear.

05:27.577 --> 05:31.289
I have to--
I have to make it look like

05:31.289 --> 05:33.667
I'm just a normal person
quitting a normal job.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.045
What about your brother?

05:37.045 --> 05:38.463
I still got two guys
with eyes on him.

05:38.463 --> 05:41.299
They'll have no reason
to hurt him

05:41.299 --> 05:43.218
if I'm leaving.

05:46.429 --> 05:47.931
Yeah.

05:47.931 --> 05:56.022
♪

05:56.022 --> 05:58.483
It's over, Scott.

05:58.483 --> 05:59.693
The Greybournes won.

05:59.693 --> 06:07.075
♪

06:07.075 --> 06:09.494
[ Door opens, closes ]

06:09.494 --> 06:18.044
♪

06:20.380 --> 06:23.967
The treasure was a baby.

06:23.967 --> 06:25.427
I'm sorry, Rome.

06:25.427 --> 06:26.970
You don't
have to be sorry.

06:26.970 --> 06:29.306
I know your dad would be proud
of you for trying so hard.

06:29.306 --> 06:30.724
I don't know.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.058
Would he?

06:32.058 --> 06:33.518
Guess who came back
last night.

06:33.518 --> 06:34.853
Hmm?
Dick Ayres.

06:34.853 --> 06:36.187
Alive?
Yep.

06:36.187 --> 06:38.148
Tory found him
in the apartment all K. O.'d.

06:38.148 --> 06:39.858
I bet that's why
they cut the power.

06:39.858 --> 06:41.109
They killed the cameras
so that no one

06:41.109 --> 06:42.694
would see them
bring him back.

06:42.694 --> 06:44.487
Yeah, my money's
still on Tory.

06:44.487 --> 06:46.406
But guess what.
She's the one who found him.

06:46.406 --> 06:47.324
The neighbors heard her screaming.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.366
Thought someone was dead.

06:48.366 --> 06:50.952
She was all over Matthew
last night.

06:50.952 --> 06:52.287
She wanted Matthew
for herself.

06:52.287 --> 06:54.205
She had to get rid of Allie
and then Dick.

06:54.205 --> 06:56.791
Okay, Sherlock,
but then why is he back?

06:56.791 --> 06:59.794
It's not our problem.

06:59.794 --> 07:01.713
When we leave, I don't think
it should be at the same time.

07:01.713 --> 07:03.423
So I'll quit.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.258
And you can wait a week.

07:05.258 --> 07:08.345
Got me?

07:08.345 --> 07:11.806
Rome, you can't stay
for Bennet.

07:11.806 --> 07:13.933
She's gonna find out.

07:13.933 --> 07:17.020
I don't know how I'm gonna
say goodbye, though.

07:17.020 --> 07:18.897
Me either.

07:20.065 --> 07:22.859
Oww! Come on.
I mean...

07:22.859 --> 07:24.277
Sorry.

07:24.277 --> 07:25.403
Stop complaining.

07:25.403 --> 07:28.156
Dr. Franklin
is doing us a favor.

07:28.156 --> 07:30.200
It's fine.

07:30.200 --> 07:32.869
No worse a patient
than Elliott.

07:32.869 --> 07:34.454
But there's a reason
why endocrinologists

07:34.454 --> 07:35.664
don't do house calls.

07:35.664 --> 07:37.082
You need a CAT scan.

07:37.082 --> 07:41.002
Oh,
and we will get him one.

07:41.002 --> 07:42.545
When his colleagues find out
he went over

07:42.545 --> 07:44.089
the handlebars
of his mountain bike,

07:44.089 --> 07:45.840
he's never gonna hear
the end of it.

07:48.760 --> 07:52.472
Okay.

07:52.472 --> 07:55.141
We'd love to have you and Craig
over for dinner sometime.

07:55.141 --> 07:56.518
And Elliott.

07:56.518 --> 07:59.020
Just text me a date
that works for you.

07:59.020 --> 08:00.438
Sure.
That'd be nice.

08:00.438 --> 08:02.816
Great.
Oh.

08:05.860 --> 08:08.446
[ Door opens, closes ]

08:11.950 --> 08:14.202
We're leaving
first thing tomorrow.

08:14.202 --> 08:15.453
Buttercup, I'm sorry.

08:15.453 --> 08:17.414
The car's
charging downstairs.

08:17.414 --> 08:19.624
I cleared out
all the bank accounts.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.126
This--
This is our home.

08:21.126 --> 08:22.794
Burn it.

08:22.794 --> 08:25.046
I hate this mausoleum.

08:25.046 --> 08:27.674
Stop, just stop, stop.

08:27.674 --> 08:31.386
Tory, you know we can't run
from these people.

08:31.386 --> 08:34.347
Anywhere
is safer than here.

08:34.347 --> 08:35.682
Otis beat you
half to death.

08:35.682 --> 08:39.436
You want to stick around
and see what happens next?

08:39.436 --> 08:41.312
I just--

08:41.312 --> 08:44.566
I just wanted to be
the one to give you

08:44.566 --> 08:48.695
and the girls a good life
and not just be a leech.

08:51.197 --> 08:53.825
I never thought of you
as a leech.

08:53.825 --> 08:55.368
The way you look at me
sometimes, Tor,

08:55.368 --> 08:56.369
I'd never know.

08:58.455 --> 09:01.416
I feel like
I have nothing,

09:01.416 --> 09:03.543
and you have everything.

09:03.543 --> 09:06.671
Right.

09:06.671 --> 09:09.758
And you only married me
because I have everything.

09:12.677 --> 09:14.095
Is that what you think?

09:17.932 --> 09:20.977
Well, that is so not true,
and it never was.

09:20.977 --> 09:23.813
I care about you, Tor, so much,
and I care about us.

09:23.813 --> 09:24.981
And sometimes
I just feel

09:24.981 --> 09:26.357
like I'm the only one here
who does.

09:26.357 --> 09:29.736
I'm trying
to keep you alive.

09:29.736 --> 09:31.404
Isn't that proof enough?

09:34.449 --> 09:35.950
That's enough.

09:39.287 --> 09:40.747
That's enough.

09:56.554 --> 09:57.555
[ Wind whooshes ]

10:06.523 --> 10:14.364
♪

10:14.364 --> 10:17.033
Please.

10:17.033 --> 10:19.035
Don't leave yet.

10:19.035 --> 10:21.287
You don't know
the whole truth.

10:21.287 --> 10:47.063
♪

10:47.063 --> 10:50.108
"Dearest Jocelyn,

10:50.108 --> 10:54.362
when I think back
on the first day we met,

10:54.362 --> 10:57.490
how little I could have known
where our paths would lead."

10:57.490 --> 11:06.249
♪ Well, you're nobody ♪

11:08.376 --> 11:11.171
♪ Until somebody loves you ♪

11:15.383 --> 11:19.179
♪ You're nobody ♪

11:19.179 --> 11:21.890
♪ Unh-unh,
till somebody cares ♪

11:26.019 --> 11:27.353
♪ You'd better mind yourself ♪

11:27.353 --> 11:31.107
[ Bell dings ]

11:31.107 --> 11:33.568
♪ You'd better find yourself ♪

11:33.568 --> 11:35.320
♪ Go out and find somebody ♪

11:35.320 --> 11:36.321
Help you, ma'am?

11:36.321 --> 11:39.240
Hello.
I'm Jocelyn Morrow.

11:39.240 --> 11:40.825
I'm here to see
the Greybournes.

11:40.825 --> 11:41.784
Certainly.

11:45.371 --> 11:47.498
[ Knock on door ]

11:47.498 --> 11:49.250
Hey.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.585
Oh, thank God it's you.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.088
Are you okay?

11:54.088 --> 11:55.757
I heard about what happened
to your dad.

11:55.757 --> 11:57.926
It's so messed up, Elena.

11:57.926 --> 11:59.844
Bennet's away, Elliott
and I aren't speaking,

11:59.844 --> 12:02.430
and I am so scared.

12:02.430 --> 12:04.891
Something terrible
is happening.

12:04.891 --> 12:07.560
And no one will tell me
the truth.

12:07.560 --> 12:09.020
Come here.

12:13.191 --> 12:16.444
[ Horns honking ]

12:16.444 --> 12:19.155
You don't have much childcare
experience, do you?

12:19.155 --> 12:21.908
No, but I practically raised
my sisters back home

12:21.908 --> 12:24.202
in County Antrim.

12:24.202 --> 12:25.620
You're a long way
from Ireland.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.291
I understand this would be
a live-in position.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.459
That's correct.

12:31.459 --> 12:32.961
May I ask
how many children

12:32.961 --> 12:34.462
you
and Mr. Greybourne have?

12:34.462 --> 12:35.755
Two.

12:35.755 --> 12:37.340
A boy and a girl.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.425
The king's choice,
they say.

12:39.425 --> 12:42.762
So I don't need any more.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.389
Would you like
to have more?

12:48.393 --> 12:50.937
I would love to.

12:50.937 --> 12:53.648
But I can't, so...

12:53.648 --> 12:56.192
"Her children arise up
and call her blessed

12:56.192 --> 12:58.903
and her husband also,
and he praiseth her."

12:58.903 --> 12:59.904
[ Door opens ]

12:59.904 --> 13:01.114
Proverbs.

13:01.114 --> 13:03.533
[ Door closes ]

13:03.533 --> 13:05.076
Can you imagine
seeing such a thing?

13:05.076 --> 13:06.327
No, and I hope
to never again.

13:06.327 --> 13:08.496
[ Laughs ]

13:08.496 --> 13:10.540
I didn't know
we had company.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.792
You did know
and you forgot.

13:15.044 --> 13:17.839
My husband,
Alistair Greybourne.

13:17.839 --> 13:20.216
And my brother,
Mr. Winthrop.

13:20.216 --> 13:21.884
Looking pretty as a picture
today, Iris.

13:21.884 --> 13:24.012
Mm, thank you.

13:24.012 --> 13:25.555
This is Miss Morrow.

13:25.555 --> 13:27.807
She's going to be
the new nanny.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.851
Oh, have I got
the job then?

13:29.851 --> 13:32.770
Yes, you can start today.

13:32.770 --> 13:34.689
I'm sure you'll be
very happy here.

13:34.689 --> 13:36.983
Thank you, Mr.
and Mrs. Greybourne.

13:36.983 --> 13:37.817
I'm sure I will.

13:40.278 --> 13:42.113
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:47.285 --> 13:53.249
Gentlemen, I can tell you
with absolute certainty

13:53.249 --> 13:55.585
Brooklyn is the future.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.420
For who?

13:57.420 --> 13:59.547
Literary hacks
and starving artists?

13:59.547 --> 14:00.923
Let them have it.

14:00.923 --> 14:02.884
Winthrop, the land is cheap.

14:02.884 --> 14:05.678
The politicians
easily purchased.

14:05.678 --> 14:09.724
The Greybourne Corporation
should plant its stake.

14:09.724 --> 14:13.227
Unless you want the Vanderbilts
to beat us to it again.

14:13.227 --> 14:15.313
Alistair,
I think it's best

14:15.313 --> 14:17.732
that our funds
stay liquid for now.

14:17.732 --> 14:20.610
Wartime and all.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.862
Marcato.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.781
What say you?

14:24.781 --> 14:26.949
We have the capital.

14:26.949 --> 14:28.618
Selling weapons
to the Allies

14:28.618 --> 14:31.537
has increased
company profits 9%.

14:31.537 --> 14:34.290
And I do agree
with Mr. Greybourne.

14:34.290 --> 14:40.546
♪

14:40.546 --> 14:42.006
Brooklyn, it is.

14:45.593 --> 14:48.679
Jocelyn: Oh, you're
an excellent shot, Bruno.

14:48.679 --> 14:51.307
Father, will you stay
and play with us?

14:51.307 --> 14:53.559
Hey, champ.

14:53.559 --> 14:56.229
Well, I'll just watch for now.

14:58.564 --> 15:00.483
Sorry for the mess, sir.

15:00.483 --> 15:02.443
I enjoy it in here.

15:02.443 --> 15:04.403
It's much simpler.

15:04.403 --> 15:06.989
Children actually
prioritize happiness.

15:06.989 --> 15:08.366
Mm.

15:08.366 --> 15:10.785
It's why I love to be
around them.

15:10.785 --> 15:12.411
Would you like children
of your own someday?

15:12.411 --> 15:14.831
I had hoped to.

15:14.831 --> 15:18.251
My husband was killed
at Dunkirk.

15:18.251 --> 15:19.877
Iris never said
you were a widow.

15:22.046 --> 15:24.423
I never told her.

15:24.423 --> 15:27.426
No respectable household
would hire a widow.

15:27.426 --> 15:28.928
But perhaps you'll be
kind enough

15:28.928 --> 15:30.429
to keep that
between us, sir.

15:30.429 --> 15:31.848
Of course.

15:31.848 --> 15:34.725
I'm sorry
for your loss.

15:45.361 --> 15:47.530
I know
you went to see Scott.

15:47.530 --> 15:49.824
You didn't leave me
any other choice.

15:49.824 --> 15:51.075
I'm not angry.

15:51.075 --> 15:52.243
I actually think
it means a lot

15:52.243 --> 15:54.287
that you would care enough
to do that.

15:54.287 --> 15:56.789
I think you'll be glad to know
I'm leaving.

15:56.789 --> 16:00.084
And Roman too.

16:00.084 --> 16:03.171
I'm sorry I lied to you
and used you.

16:03.171 --> 16:05.840
I never meant to hurt you
or any one of our friends.

16:07.216 --> 16:10.636
So just please
let everyone know that.

16:10.636 --> 16:13.931
So you want me to tell Alex
and James and Kim and Elliott

16:13.931 --> 16:17.226
and Darcy and Bennet,
who all loved and trusted you,

16:17.226 --> 16:18.436
by the way,
that you lied to us?

16:18.436 --> 16:20.021
That's my job?

16:20.021 --> 16:22.773
You guys can just go back
to the way it was

16:22.773 --> 16:24.692
before I came in
and messed everything up.

16:24.692 --> 16:25.985
You are kidding yourself

16:25.985 --> 16:29.071
if you think
that is even possible.

16:29.071 --> 16:30.823
I hope
it was all worth it.

16:30.823 --> 16:34.785
♪

16:39.373 --> 16:42.668
♪ I was a giver ♪

16:42.668 --> 16:44.378
What's the occasion?

16:44.378 --> 16:46.130
To say I'm sorry
for meddling with Darcy

16:46.130 --> 16:48.841
and that I'm leaving.

16:48.841 --> 16:50.218
Oh, you're leaving?

16:50.218 --> 16:53.763
Family emergency.

16:53.763 --> 16:57.892
Honestly, I thought
you would be glad,

16:57.892 --> 17:00.603
considering my very
crummy advice

17:00.603 --> 17:02.939
that ruined your summer
of love.

17:02.939 --> 17:06.651
Yeah, I've been told
I can be pedantic.

17:06.651 --> 17:08.069
Sorry for blowing up
at you.

17:08.069 --> 17:10.238
Oh, no worries.

17:10.238 --> 17:14.784
You and me,
friends for life.

17:14.784 --> 17:17.370
But you and Darcy.

17:17.370 --> 17:20.373
Just tell her
how you feel.

17:20.373 --> 17:21.999
I get the feeling
she's tired of people

17:21.999 --> 17:25.628
keeping secrets
from her.

17:25.628 --> 17:28.506
♪ It's the only way out ♪

17:28.506 --> 17:30.925
[ Thunder rumbling softly ]

17:34.554 --> 17:37.014
[ Lightning crashes ]

17:52.280 --> 17:54.365
Jocelyn:
What a clever trick.

17:54.365 --> 17:56.409
Miss Morrow,
I didn't see you there.

17:56.409 --> 17:58.578
How does it work?

17:58.578 --> 18:01.998
The mechanism?

18:01.998 --> 18:04.917
I had a watchmaker create it
for me, actually,

18:04.917 --> 18:06.502
to hide this key.

18:06.502 --> 18:08.296
What's it for?

18:08.296 --> 18:10.298
Treasure chest?

18:10.298 --> 18:12.216
Nothing so special.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.968
Just a cabinet where
I keep my papers away

18:13.968 --> 18:16.637
from the prying eyes
of my partners.

18:16.637 --> 18:18.014
Like Mr. Winthrop?

18:18.014 --> 18:19.765
Him and others.

18:19.765 --> 18:20.683
[ Lightning crashes ]

18:20.683 --> 18:22.852
[ Gasps ]

18:22.852 --> 18:25.521
Don't be scared.
I'm not scared.

18:27.607 --> 18:31.652
Do you feel the charge
in the air?

18:31.652 --> 18:33.029
Particles of energy.

18:33.029 --> 18:35.990
Like-- Like magic.

18:35.990 --> 18:44.957
♪

18:44.957 --> 18:46.542
I don't think
I've ever met

18:46.542 --> 18:49.420
anyone like you,
Jocelyn Morrow.

18:49.420 --> 18:54.508
♪

18:54.508 --> 18:55.843
[ Elevator bell dings ]

19:00.389 --> 19:02.099
Ginny: [ Giggles ]

19:02.099 --> 19:04.560
Oh. Do not get near
an open flame.

19:04.560 --> 19:06.520
I can still smell
the fumes on you.

19:06.520 --> 19:08.314
Okay, I was stuck
in an elevator

19:08.314 --> 19:09.649
with a bottle of mezcal.

19:09.649 --> 19:13.277
What was I supposed to do,
not drink it?

19:13.277 --> 19:14.612
At least someone had
a good night.

19:14.612 --> 19:16.447
Kim practically danced
her way to the airport

19:16.447 --> 19:17.782
because of you.

19:17.782 --> 19:19.450
Meanwhile,
I'm stuck stateside

19:19.450 --> 19:22.036
with the one kid
who's afraid of flying.

19:22.036 --> 19:23.245
I don't want
to mess it up.

19:23.245 --> 19:26.040
Babe, you could never.
You're great.

19:26.040 --> 19:29.502
I have a lengthy history
of being not so great.

19:29.502 --> 19:30.920
What did you want
to talk about?

19:33.464 --> 19:35.216
Okay.

19:35.216 --> 19:36.592
When I was stuck
in the elevator

19:36.592 --> 19:39.220
with James and Mrs. Ivey,
I kind of got the vibe

19:39.220 --> 19:42.056
that they, like,
already know each other.

19:42.056 --> 19:44.016
How well do you
really know James?

19:44.016 --> 19:49.772
♪

19:49.772 --> 19:51.273
I've missed you.

19:51.273 --> 19:52.775
It's impossible
to get away.

19:55.444 --> 19:57.113
We can't keep lying
to her.

19:57.113 --> 19:58.739
She has no idea.

19:58.739 --> 20:01.492
She will...

20:01.492 --> 20:04.412
soon...

20:04.412 --> 20:07.540
when she sees.

20:07.540 --> 20:09.875
How far along are you?

20:09.875 --> 20:11.711
A few months.

20:11.711 --> 20:14.714
It'll be Ruby
if it's a girl.

20:14.714 --> 20:17.091
After my mother.

20:17.091 --> 20:19.427
Ruby's a fine name.

20:19.427 --> 20:22.805
My God,
what are we gonna do?

20:22.805 --> 20:25.558
I have to leave.

20:25.558 --> 20:28.060
Jocelyn, no.

20:28.060 --> 20:30.563
You can't go.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.148
But I can't stay either.

20:36.193 --> 20:38.612
Iris:
Who is the father?

20:38.612 --> 20:41.240
Just a man I met.

20:41.240 --> 20:42.658
He's gone now.

20:42.658 --> 20:43.993
Coward.

20:43.993 --> 20:45.494
I want to thank you,
Mrs. Greybourne,

20:45.494 --> 20:47.455
for all your kindness
to me.

20:47.455 --> 20:50.916
I'm so sorry
I let you down.

20:50.916 --> 20:53.252
I won't bring shame
upon your home.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.713
God bless you
and your children.

21:00.217 --> 21:02.178
The world will be unkind
to you, Jocelyn.

21:04.764 --> 21:06.348
Your reputation
will be ruined

21:06.348 --> 21:08.184
and your child
will starve.

21:10.019 --> 21:12.396
Unless he became
a Greybourne.

21:14.398 --> 21:16.233
He would have
every advantage.

21:16.233 --> 21:19.236
The best school, the best
marriage prospects,

21:19.236 --> 21:21.655
a bright future.

21:21.655 --> 21:23.240
If the child was mine
and not yours.

21:23.240 --> 21:25.075
It's not a he.

21:25.075 --> 21:28.329
It's a she,
and she's mine.

21:28.329 --> 21:29.205
I won't abandon her.

21:29.205 --> 21:31.081
You wouldn't have to.

21:31.081 --> 21:34.376
You could raise her
as her nanny.

21:34.376 --> 21:38.964
No one would know the truth
except us.

21:38.964 --> 21:41.258
And Alistair and Otis.

21:41.258 --> 21:45.095
We would have to keep it
from everyone else, you see.

21:45.095 --> 21:49.308
Alistair lost everything
in the crash in 1929.

21:49.308 --> 21:52.353
And my father bailed him
out on one condition--

21:52.353 --> 21:53.813
that only legitimate heirs

21:53.813 --> 21:55.815
would inherit
the family fortune.

21:55.815 --> 21:58.984
He never liked Alistair.
He never trusted him.

21:58.984 --> 22:03.197
As long as we claim
that the baby is mine,

22:03.197 --> 22:05.282
she will become
a true Greybourne.

22:05.282 --> 22:10.079
♪

22:10.079 --> 22:13.082
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

22:22.424 --> 22:47.199
♪

22:47.199 --> 22:49.285
Elena:
What happened to you, Ruby?

22:56.125 --> 23:12.391
♪

23:12.391 --> 23:15.269
I-I know I messed up.

23:15.269 --> 23:20.149
But I really like you, Darcy.

23:20.149 --> 23:22.651
And I want to say sorry.

23:24.320 --> 23:27.114
♪ We'll make music
in the morning ♪

23:29.366 --> 23:31.076
I'm really glad
you're here.

23:31.076 --> 23:35.456
♪ And when this life feels
like it's too much to bear ♪

23:35.456 --> 23:41.712
♪ I hope you share ♪

23:41.712 --> 23:42.963
Everything okay?

23:42.963 --> 23:44.632
Flora's parents didn't call,
did they?

23:44.632 --> 23:47.092
Uh, no, everything
is fine with Jasper,

23:47.092 --> 23:49.470
but, um...

23:49.470 --> 23:52.056
it's about my brother.

23:52.056 --> 23:54.141
What, is he okay?

23:54.141 --> 23:55.851
No, not really.

23:55.851 --> 23:58.354
He got into some trouble
at school, big trouble,

23:58.354 --> 24:01.982
and I, um, have to leave
tomorrow to deal with it.

24:01.982 --> 24:03.525
Yeah. Go. Go.

24:03.525 --> 24:04.443
I mean, take as much time
as you need.

24:04.443 --> 24:06.028
We'll manage.

24:06.028 --> 24:07.821
Just shoot me a text when
you're ready to come back.

24:09.990 --> 24:11.158
I won't be coming back.

24:13.160 --> 24:14.870
Wait, what?

24:14.870 --> 24:17.247
I can't.

24:17.247 --> 24:18.958
My brother needs me.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.417
I called the nanny agency, though,

24:20.417 --> 24:22.169
and they'll get
a temp tomorrow

24:22.169 --> 24:25.089
until you can find
someone permanent.

24:27.633 --> 24:32.054
I'm-- I'm so sorry, Matthew.

24:32.054 --> 24:34.181
Uh...[sighs]

24:34.181 --> 24:35.683
Yeah. No,
I'm sorry, too.

24:38.185 --> 24:39.853
God, this is gonna
break Jasper's heart.

24:42.231 --> 24:43.691
I know.

24:45.859 --> 24:48.404
I really feel like

24:48.404 --> 24:51.115
he's really blooming
this summer

24:51.115 --> 24:54.618
after everything
that's happened.

24:54.618 --> 24:56.745
He's a lot stronger
than we know.

24:56.745 --> 24:58.580
Yeah, because of you, Elena.

25:02.501 --> 25:05.045
Is there anything I can do
to convince you to come back?

25:07.965 --> 25:10.092
No.

25:10.092 --> 25:11.593
Okay.

25:14.263 --> 25:16.098
Um, do you think
you could stick around

25:16.098 --> 25:18.642
just so Jasper
could say goodbye?

25:18.642 --> 25:20.894
Just for some closure?

25:20.894 --> 25:23.897
Yeah.
I'll come by in the morning.

25:23.897 --> 25:26.066
Is that okay?

25:26.066 --> 25:28.527
Thank you.

25:28.527 --> 25:31.613
And I'll, uh, I'll break
the news to him.

25:31.613 --> 25:33.115
That way,
you won't have to.

25:33.115 --> 25:34.700
Okay.

25:34.700 --> 25:40.080
♪

25:40.080 --> 25:41.540
I'm gonna go grab a sweater

25:41.540 --> 25:43.959
that I left in his room
before I forget, okay?

25:47.087 --> 25:49.173
Jocelyn:
♪ Lilies o'er spread ♪

25:49.173 --> 25:52.468
♪ In baby's wee bed ♪

25:52.468 --> 26:04.480
♪

26:04.480 --> 26:08.525
Our Ruby.

26:08.525 --> 26:10.903
I don't know how much longer
I can keep this up.

26:12.571 --> 26:15.699
Playing nanny
to my own daughter.

26:15.699 --> 26:18.368
It's too painful.

26:18.368 --> 26:21.580
She has her eyes,
your smile.

26:23.791 --> 26:25.292
No one can ever
take that away.

26:25.292 --> 26:41.016
♪

26:41.016 --> 26:42.976
Run away?

26:42.976 --> 26:44.436
What are you,
16 and pregnant?

26:44.436 --> 26:46.438
Grown women
don't run away.

26:46.438 --> 26:49.691
My husband was beaten
within an inch of his life

26:49.691 --> 26:51.860
by your business partner.

26:51.860 --> 26:53.695
You said he was fine.

26:53.695 --> 26:55.697
I said he was alive.

26:55.697 --> 26:58.283
Nothing is fine.

26:58.283 --> 27:01.078
Otis isn't gonna stop.
He's dangerous.

27:01.078 --> 27:02.371
He's family.

27:02.371 --> 27:04.414
I'm calling the police.
You will not.

27:09.920 --> 27:12.756
Aunt Charlotte, I've been
going over it in my head,

27:12.756 --> 27:14.550
and it still doesn't
make any sense.

27:14.550 --> 27:17.636
What if Allie
didn't kill herself?

27:17.636 --> 27:19.304
What if someone else
hurt her?

27:19.304 --> 27:21.014
Someone like Otis.

27:23.308 --> 27:28.063
What happened to your sister
was a terrible tragedy.

27:28.063 --> 27:30.607
But if you're looking
for someone to blame,

27:30.607 --> 27:32.901
the only person
to blame is Allie.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.034
Mm.

27:43.954 --> 27:46.832
I don't know what I'd do
without you, Aunt Charlotte.

27:46.832 --> 27:48.292
Neither do I.

27:56.592 --> 27:59.344
But I'm so scared.
It's my fault.

27:59.344 --> 28:00.971
I never meant
to hurt her.

28:00.971 --> 28:03.098
I know.
But she knows.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.976
Iris knows.

28:05.976 --> 28:07.978
She's told me to leave.

28:07.978 --> 28:09.438
What am I gonna do?

28:09.438 --> 28:11.899
Ruby's a Greybourne now.
Iris will never let her go.

28:14.234 --> 28:16.194
Ruby's birth certificate.

28:16.194 --> 28:18.155
She's yours now.

28:18.155 --> 28:19.740
And so am I.

28:19.740 --> 28:21.867
Let's run away together.

28:21.867 --> 28:25.370
The three of us.

28:25.370 --> 28:26.788
Alistair.

28:26.788 --> 28:28.540
Hide this
in the staircase.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.417
Iris will destroy it
if she ever finds it.

28:32.878 --> 28:36.089
I'll bring Ruby.
I'll meet you there at midnight.

28:36.089 --> 28:38.008
We'll be penniless.

28:38.008 --> 28:39.259
Will you still love me?

28:39.259 --> 28:44.389
♪

28:44.389 --> 28:46.558
Always and forever.

28:52.481 --> 28:53.690
I stalked all
of James' socials.

28:53.690 --> 28:55.317
Nothing seems shady.

28:55.317 --> 28:57.235
What, you think
he's cheating on you?

28:57.235 --> 28:58.195
Oh, we're not exclusive.

28:58.195 --> 28:59.863
He could do
whatever he wants.

28:59.863 --> 29:01.615
Except lie.

29:01.615 --> 29:02.741
Okay, like today,
he said

29:02.741 --> 29:04.159
he's with the Patels
at their place

29:04.159 --> 29:08.372
in Watch Hill,
but is he really?

29:08.372 --> 29:10.874
Only one way to find out.
Call Zora Patel.

29:10.874 --> 29:13.710
I have her number from when Rex
did golf clinic with her kids.

29:13.710 --> 29:16.046
Just tell her you got
her number from Julie Quinn.

29:16.046 --> 29:17.130
[ Cellphone rings ]

29:17.130 --> 29:19.299
Wait, what if he's
actually there?

29:19.299 --> 29:21.760
You're the actor. Improv.

29:21.760 --> 29:23.762
If we record this,
can I use it for my reel?

29:23.762 --> 29:25.347
Zora Patel.
Uh, hello.

29:25.347 --> 29:29.601
My name is
Alexandra... Ginny.

29:29.601 --> 29:31.812
I got your number
from Julie Quinn

29:31.812 --> 29:34.272
because I'm trying
to reach your manny, James.

29:34.272 --> 29:36.274
I'm interested in setting up
some piano lessons

29:36.274 --> 29:37.818
with him for my son.

29:37.818 --> 29:39.820
And, um,
I tried his number,

29:39.820 --> 29:41.363
but there was no answer.

29:41.363 --> 29:42.572
Julie mentioned that

29:42.572 --> 29:44.616
you're all in Watch Hill
together, so...

29:44.616 --> 29:46.618
Oh, God.
I'm sorry.

29:46.618 --> 29:48.120
This is so awkward.

29:48.120 --> 29:50.163
But James doesn't work
for us anymore.

29:50.163 --> 29:52.582
He was incredibly unreliable.

29:52.582 --> 29:54.793
We had to let him go
a few months back.

29:54.793 --> 29:56.044
You did?

29:56.044 --> 29:57.713
Sorry I can't be
more helpful.

29:57.713 --> 29:59.464
Please tell Julie
I said hello.

30:02.217 --> 30:04.302
He hasn't worked
for them in months?

30:04.302 --> 30:05.929
Mnh-mnh.

30:05.929 --> 30:08.557
Found it.

30:08.557 --> 30:11.768
So, what's next
for Elena?

30:11.768 --> 30:14.354
I'll probably just go
finish packing.

30:14.354 --> 30:16.732
No, I mean, in life.

30:16.732 --> 30:19.359
You talked about
getting your college degree.

30:19.359 --> 30:21.528
That still on the table?

30:21.528 --> 30:24.364
Yeah, that's gonna have
to wait.

30:24.364 --> 30:25.824
Well, you got
somewhere to stay?

30:25.824 --> 30:27.659
Family?

30:27.659 --> 30:31.038
Um, no, not really.

30:31.038 --> 30:32.581
Boyfriend?

30:35.125 --> 30:38.795
I had someone,
but that's over.

30:38.795 --> 30:40.797
And I didn't say anything
in the interview

30:40.797 --> 30:44.593
because it was
already rocky and...

30:47.095 --> 30:50.015
So what happened?

30:50.015 --> 30:52.267
You know, the usual.

30:52.267 --> 30:55.771
We fought all the time,
mostly about money.

30:55.771 --> 30:58.607
It got exhausting.

30:58.607 --> 31:00.108
And after a while,
I didn't really know

31:00.108 --> 31:01.777
what we were
fighting about.

31:01.777 --> 31:03.820
Yeah.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.198
People fight about money
more than anything else.

31:06.198 --> 31:07.657
That's what did us in.

31:07.657 --> 31:10.744
Allie and me.

31:10.744 --> 31:12.120
You know,
before I met her,

31:12.120 --> 31:13.038
I never had more
than 1,000 bucks

31:13.038 --> 31:15.332
in my bank account.

31:15.332 --> 31:18.418
She came
from all of this.

31:18.418 --> 31:19.795
I just wanted
to take Jasper

31:19.795 --> 31:21.713
and go back to Indiana
just to keep him grounded,

31:21.713 --> 31:23.215
but she didn't want
to leave this.

31:25.634 --> 31:28.512
That's why we were
gonna split.

31:28.512 --> 31:30.639
I'm so sorry.

31:30.639 --> 31:33.517
I mean, we still loved
each other, but we just--

31:33.517 --> 31:37.854
we both wanted to be
on our own home planets.

31:37.854 --> 31:39.189
I wasn't gonna get a dime.

31:39.189 --> 31:40.524
Ironclad pre-nup.

31:40.524 --> 31:43.276
And I was so fine
with that.

31:45.320 --> 31:47.489
And then she died,
and I got it all.

31:49.908 --> 31:53.578
Here I am, still
at The Greybourne.

31:56.665 --> 31:59.543
I'm glad you didn't run off
to Indiana.

31:59.543 --> 32:01.837
Why's that?

32:01.837 --> 32:03.213
Because I wouldn't
have met you.

32:06.174 --> 32:08.426
♪ If looks could kill ♪

32:08.426 --> 32:14.683
♪ Deadly ♪

32:14.683 --> 32:17.602
♪ Something of desire ♪

32:17.602 --> 32:19.104
♪ Needed ♪

32:19.104 --> 32:20.856
♪ Badly ♪

32:20.856 --> 32:23.525
♪ Passion is a fire ♪

32:23.525 --> 32:25.902
♪ All it takes is just a look ♪

32:25.902 --> 32:28.655
♪ All it takes is one ♪

32:28.655 --> 32:31.700
♪ To captivate and pull you in ♪

32:31.700 --> 32:34.995
♪ Your time has come ♪

32:34.995 --> 32:37.831
♪ All it takes is
just a stare ♪

32:37.831 --> 32:40.876
Where are you, Alistair?

32:40.876 --> 32:43.920
♪ I'm slowly gonna do you in ♪

32:43.920 --> 32:46.548
♪ Your time has come ♪

32:46.548 --> 32:48.675
♪ If looks could kill ♪

32:52.596 --> 32:55.307
♪ If looks could kill ♪

32:58.852 --> 33:00.353
♪ If looks could kill ♪

33:00.353 --> 33:05.066
♪ Wouldn't it be, oh,
such a thrill? ♪

33:05.066 --> 33:07.485
♪ If looks could kill ♪

33:07.485 --> 33:09.779
♪

33:11.865 --> 33:30.300
♪

33:30.300 --> 33:32.802
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

33:32.802 --> 33:35.513
It's alright.

33:35.513 --> 33:37.265
Shh, shh, shh, it's alright.

33:37.265 --> 33:38.725
Here we are.

33:43.271 --> 33:44.773
Iris: Hey.
Hey, what are you doing?

33:44.773 --> 33:46.316
Jocelyn,
put that baby down.

33:47.484 --> 33:50.153
[ Baby crying ]

33:50.153 --> 33:51.655
Jocelyn!

33:55.867 --> 33:56.910
Give her back to me.

33:56.910 --> 33:58.161
Stay away from us!

33:58.161 --> 33:59.704
She is mine!
No!

33:59.704 --> 34:07.587
♪

34:12.801 --> 34:14.177
I should go.

34:16.346 --> 34:17.847
What?

34:23.895 --> 34:27.232
You know what?
Um...

34:27.232 --> 34:28.692
You don't have to go.

34:31.111 --> 34:32.153
I do.

34:36.199 --> 34:37.659
I'm scared.

34:40.161 --> 34:41.079
Look, I know, okay?

34:41.079 --> 34:43.206
I'm-- I'm scared, too.

34:44.833 --> 34:47.002
I hope you and Jasper
make it back to Indiana.

34:47.002 --> 34:56.636
♪

34:56.636 --> 34:57.929
I never touched her.

34:57.929 --> 35:01.474
[ Jocelyn groaning ]

35:01.474 --> 35:03.226
Alistair was gonna
run away with her.

35:08.189 --> 35:09.274
What are we gonna do?

35:12.611 --> 35:14.654
What are you doing?
She's still alive.

35:14.654 --> 35:18.074
♪

35:18.074 --> 35:19.743
[ Body thuds ]

35:22.954 --> 35:26.333
Aaah!

35:26.333 --> 35:28.627
Just another suicide
nobody's gonna care about.

35:28.627 --> 35:57.322
♪

35:57.322 --> 36:00.450
You will not destroy
everything we built

36:00.450 --> 36:03.328
and bring shame
upon my sister.

36:03.328 --> 36:23.431
♪

36:23.431 --> 36:26.685
Elena: Mrs. Ivey, did you
hear anything strange

36:26.685 --> 36:27.727
last night?

36:27.727 --> 36:30.605
After the blackout.

36:30.605 --> 36:32.190
Not a thing.
Why do you ask?

36:35.235 --> 36:38.613
It doesn't matter anymore.

36:38.613 --> 36:40.490
I'm here to tell you

36:40.490 --> 36:43.451
that I'm leaving
The Greybourne.

36:43.451 --> 36:46.121
Matthew didn't
kill his wife.

36:46.121 --> 36:48.498
You're wrong about him.

36:48.498 --> 36:50.500
He and Allie were filing
for divorce,

36:50.500 --> 36:51.876
and he wasn't gonna
get anything

36:51.876 --> 36:55.004
because of the pre-nup,
and he was fine with it.

36:55.004 --> 36:57.590
He told you that?

36:57.590 --> 36:59.175
Might he be lying?

36:59.175 --> 37:01.678
My bullshit radar
is pretty good.

37:01.678 --> 37:04.472
Well, I'm sorry you weren't
able to discover

37:04.472 --> 37:07.058
anything
more illuminating.

37:07.058 --> 37:08.309
I hope you've enjoyed living

37:08.309 --> 37:10.895
at The Greybourne,
however briefly.

37:10.895 --> 37:13.314
My father was
very proud of it.

37:13.314 --> 37:15.066
Was he?

37:15.066 --> 37:18.319
Shame he had a massive heart
attack right after I was born.

37:18.319 --> 37:20.864
Tragedy seems to run
in our family.

37:20.864 --> 37:24.242
I'm the only one left
to carry on his legacy now.

37:24.242 --> 37:26.327
And Jasper, eventually.

37:26.327 --> 37:29.038
Goodbye, Mrs. Ivey.

37:29.038 --> 37:30.540
Miss Santos.

37:34.169 --> 37:38.465
Whatever you're running from,
you may as well face it

37:38.465 --> 37:40.467
since it's going to catch up
with you anyway.

37:40.467 --> 37:53.938
♪

37:53.938 --> 37:55.815
[ Whispers ]
Goodbye, Jocelyn.

37:55.815 --> 38:13.333
♪

38:13.333 --> 38:16.461
A tragic
double suicide then?

38:16.461 --> 38:18.463
It would seem that way, Officer.

38:20.423 --> 38:21.841
It's a terrible thing.

38:21.841 --> 38:24.135
I got to tell you.

38:24.135 --> 38:26.346
[ Clears throat ]

38:26.346 --> 38:28.556
It would absolutely kill
my sister

38:28.556 --> 38:31.142
if a connection
to these two misfortunes

38:31.142 --> 38:32.769
ever made it out
to the press.

38:32.769 --> 38:34.771
The shame on the family.

38:34.771 --> 38:36.064
She's already bereaved.

38:36.064 --> 38:37.482
You understand, don't
you?

38:40.860 --> 38:42.028
That can be arranged.

38:42.028 --> 39:02.423
♪

39:02.423 --> 39:04.676
I'm so sorry
for your loss, ma'am.

39:07.512 --> 39:08.805
She's beautiful.

39:08.805 --> 39:09.722
What's her name?

39:13.101 --> 39:14.519
Charlotte.

39:14.519 --> 39:17.522
Who's that in that photo?

39:17.522 --> 39:18.731
My family.

39:18.731 --> 39:20.567
And who's that woman?

39:20.567 --> 39:22.902
Oh, the nanny, Jocelyn.

39:22.902 --> 39:25.864
I don't remember her.
She died when I was baby.

39:25.864 --> 39:33.037
♪

39:33.037 --> 39:35.039
[ Door opens ]

39:35.039 --> 39:38.084
[ Door closes ]

39:38.084 --> 39:40.628
[ Jocelyn crying ]

39:52.348 --> 39:54.434
[ Crying continues ]

40:06.112 --> 40:08.656
[ Brahms' "Lullaby" playing ]

40:08.656 --> 40:21.210
♪

40:21.210 --> 40:24.005
[ Crying continues ]

40:24.005 --> 40:27.300
Ruby, my Ruby.

40:27.300 --> 40:35.099
♪

40:35.099 --> 40:36.601
What the hell?

40:36.601 --> 40:38.770
Ruby Greybourne
is Charlotte Ivey.

40:38.770 --> 40:41.356
Charlotte Ivey,
like Mrs. Ivey?

40:41.356 --> 40:43.691
Jocelyn and Alistair
named the baby Ruby.

40:43.691 --> 40:45.193
But when Iris,
Alistair's wife,

40:45.193 --> 40:47.070
took the baby and pretended
it was hers,

40:47.070 --> 40:49.447
she changed her name
to Charlotte.

40:49.447 --> 40:51.491
Okay, that's truly wild,
but what does it matter?

40:51.491 --> 40:53.868
Mrs. Ivey is a Greybourne,

40:53.868 --> 40:55.411
but she's not a Winthrop.

40:55.411 --> 40:57.121
And the money came
through the Winthrops,

40:57.121 --> 40:59.707
and you have to be a legitimate
heir in order to inherit.

40:59.707 --> 41:01.334
So either Ivey knows that,

41:01.334 --> 41:03.294
and she's got
everybody fooled.

41:03.294 --> 41:05.755
Or she doesn't know.
And she will soon.

41:05.755 --> 41:07.924
I think Jocelyn has
been trying to tell me

41:07.924 --> 41:10.343
to protect her baby.

41:10.343 --> 41:13.346
But Ruby is not
a baby anymore.

41:13.346 --> 41:16.516
And I got
to protect my own.

41:16.516 --> 41:18.685
I bet Ivey will pay
to keep that a secret.

41:18.685 --> 41:20.103
The question is how much?

41:23.064 --> 41:24.232
We're not leaving
The Greybourne

41:24.232 --> 41:27.443
until we spin this paper
into gold.

41:30.989 --> 41:55.596
♪
